The default table display of `Get-PSDrive` displays the `DisplayRoot` property value  as `Root` unless it is empty. You can see this behavior by piping your `Get-PSDrive` to `Format-List *`. To control the output, you can use a calculated property with [Select-Object][1].

    Get-PSDrive -Name X | Select-Object @{
        Name=&#39;Root&#39;
        Expression = {
            if ([string]::IsNullOrEmpty($_.DisplayRoot)) {
                $_.Root
            }
            else {
                $_.DisplayRoot
            }
        }
    }

**Explanation:**

If you check the `$pshome\PowerShellCore.format.ps1xml` file, it defines the root value with the following expression, which is why you see this behavior.

    if($_.DisplayRoot -ne $null) { $_.DisplayRoot } else { $_.Root }

