There is no built-in method, but there are third-party libraries that offer this functionality. The [MoreLinq][1] is a respected and free .NET library that offers a [`WindowLeft`][2] extension method, that processes a sequence into a series of subsequences representing a windowed subset of the original. So you could use it to process your phraseSources in pairs, and discard the pairs that have two equal phrases. Finally select the first phrase of the pairs that survived.

    using static MoreLinq.Extensions.WindowLeftExtension;

    var phraseSources2 = phraseSources
